<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-12-0788 </DOCNO><TEXT>To gain a clear insight into the discrepancy between environment policyand economic policy the Dutch Economic Institute and the engineeringconsultants of Comprimo executed an investigation in order to map thepossible effects of environment measures on the economy in the Rijnmond,Netherlands, aimed at the refinery sector. A mixed quantitative/qualitativemethod has been used to examine to what extent the competitiveness ofa Rijnmond refinery, compared to a refinery in Belgium and one in WesternGermany, can be affected by cost-raising environment measures. This articlereports the results. Also the development of the environmental policyas well as the oil refinery industry in Western Europe is outlined. 8refs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>